{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"score\": 0.9999999998067324, \"rank\": 1.931720919381633e-10, \"text\": \"Orange\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\"}, {\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2223850069292373e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Four companies\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"Videtics\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"ChapsVision\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1345}, {\"ngram\": \"Wintics\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"algorithms\", \"from\": 1397, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"analyse video streams\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1432}, {\"ngram\": \"existing video surveillance systems\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1480}, {\"ngram\": \"potential threats\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1515}, {\"ngram\": \"public spaces\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1532}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The algorithms are trained to detect pre-determined \\\"events\\\" and abnormal behaviour and send alerts accordingly.\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The algorithms\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"pre-determined \\\"events\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1594}, {\"ngram\": \"abnormal behaviour\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1618}, {\"ngram\": \"alerts\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Human beings then decide if the alert is real and whether to act on it.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1719, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Human beings\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"the alert\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WHAT WILL THE ALGORITHMS BE LOOKING FOR?\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"THE ALGORITHMS\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1745}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The law allows for eight different \\\"events\\\" to be flagged by AI surveillance software during the Games that include: crowd surges; abnormally heavy crowds; abandoned objects; presence or use of weapons; a person on the ground; a fire breaking out; contravention of rules on traffic direction.\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 2055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1824, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2223850069292373e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The law\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1770}, {\"ngram\": \"eight different \\\"events\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1805}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1865}, {\"ngram\": \"crowd surges\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1892}, {\"ngram\": \"abnormally heavy crowds\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"abandoned objects\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"presence\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1946}, {\"ngram\": \"use\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1953}, {\"ngram\": \"weapons\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1964}, {\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"a fire\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 1996}, {\"ngram\": \"contravention\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2024}, {\"ngram\": \"rules\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"traffic direction\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Within these categories, specific thresholds (number of people, type of vehicle, timing etc) can be set manually to cater for each individual event, location or threat.\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2225, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these categories\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2080}, {\"ngram\": \"specific thresholds\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"number\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2119}, {\"ngram\": \"type\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2125}, {\"ngram\": \"vehicle\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"each individual event\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"location\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2214}, {\"ngram\": \"threat\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WHO WILL USE AI-POWERED SURVEILLANCE?\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"AI-POWERED SURVEILLANCE\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National and local police, firefighters, public transport security agents will all have access to AI-powered surveillance.\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"National and local police\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"firefighters\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2305}, {\"ngram\": \"public transport security agents\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2360}, {\"ngram\": \"AI-powered surveillance\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Software developed by Wintics and tested at the Depeche Mode concert, will be deployed in the Paris region and on public transport.\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996216502, \"rank\": 3.7823768756707857e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Software\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"Wintics\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2419}, {\"ngram\": \"the Depeche Mode concert\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2458}, {\"ngram\": \"public transport\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2520}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Police chief Laurent Nunez described the trial as largely a success.\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2523, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996216502, \"rank\": 3.7823768756707857e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the trial\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"largely a success\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2596}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everything went relatively well, all the lights are green (for future use),\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everything\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"all the lights\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2647}, {\"ngram\": \"future use\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WILL FACIAL RECOGNITION BE USED?\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2719, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It should not.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2735, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new law continues to ban facial recognition in most cases and French authorities have said it is a red line not to be crossed.\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2802, \"end\": 2808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8251309150701409, \"rank\": 0.20750005985859915, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The new law\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2747}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 2765, \"to\": 2783}, {\"ngram\": \"most cases\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2797}, {\"ngram\": \"a red line\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonetheless, rights campaigners are concerned mission creep risks setting in down the line.\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rights campaigners\", \"from\": 2881, \"to\": 2899}, {\"ngram\": \"concerned mission creep risks\", \"from\": 2904, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 2958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Software that enables AI-powered video surveillance can easily enable facial recognition.\", \"from\": 2961, \"to\": 3051, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Software\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2970}, {\"ngram\": \"AI-powered video surveillance\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 3013}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's simply a configuration choice,\\\" said Katia Roux of Amnesty International France.\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3094, \"end\": 3099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\", \"score\": 0.9999999907245183, \"rank\": 9.275695122632006e-09, \"text\": \"Katia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\"}, {\"begin\": 3108, \"end\": 3129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.1243370930011012e-12, \"text\": \"Amnesty International\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\"}, {\"begin\": 3130, \"end\": 3136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9991906665866568, \"rank\": 0.0004628706251213083, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a configuration choice\", \"from\": 3064, \"to\": 3086}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legal framework regulating facial recognition remained too fuzzy and technical and legal safeguards were insufficient, according to Amnesty International.\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3275, \"end\": 3296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.1243370930011012e-12, \"text\": \"Amnesty International\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The legal framework\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3158}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 3170, \"to\": 3188}, {\"ngram\": \"too fuzzy and technical and legal safeguards\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3242}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wintics Co-founder Matthias Houllier said his software's algorithms were not trained for facial recognition.\", \"from\": 3299, \"to\": 3407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3318, \"end\": 3326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\", \"score\": 0.9928929403076393, \"rank\": 0.006459358356763161, \"text\": \"Matthias\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his software's algorithms\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3366}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 3388, \"to\": 3406}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no personal identification method in our algorithms,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no personal identification method\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3452}, {\"ngram\": \"our algorithms\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\